title: Grateful Dead Live at Niagara Falls Convention Center on 1984-04-17
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Adobe Audition 3.0 > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Dire Wolf, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, My Brother Esau, Ramble On Rose, Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

Beer Barrel Polka, Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Women Are Smarter-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Touch Of Gray

reviews.review_text:
OUTSTANDING sound Thank you for posting another version of a super fun night in my life and tour. 
 This sounds great to me having listened threw rhythm devils portion to this point. I give the sound 5 stars because it seems the taper was for sure in the rite spot . Considering the boys had never played here you nailed the sound.  Thank you very much for posting this.
Blown away This show is incredible. I can not stop listening to it.
